{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01VJ1uVXg5ChdtM9VX39Paxc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018SdHHLVGNrA8LrkXVKpGnf","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Read Excel vendor data","subagent_type":"general-purpose","prompt":"Read the Excel file at C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx and extract ALL rows from the \"Vendor Analysis Assessment\" sheet. I need:\n1. The exact column headers\n2. Every row of data, specifically the vendor name column and the \"Last 12 months Cost (USD)\" column\n\nUse the Bash tool to run a Python script to read the Excel file and print all rows. Here's the script to run:\n\n```python\nimport openpyxl\nwb = openpyxl.load_workbook(r'C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx', data_only=True)\nprint(\"Sheet names:\", wb.sheetnames)\nws = None\nfor name in wb.sheetnames:\n    if 'Vendor' in name and 'Assessment' in name:\n        ws = wb[name]\n        break\nif ws is None:\n    ws = wb.active\nprint(f\"Using sheet: {ws.title}\")\nprint(f\"Dimensions: {ws.dimensions}\")\n# Print headers (row 1)\nheaders = [cell.value for cell in ws[1]]\nprint(\"Headers:\", headers)\n# Print first 5 rows to understand structure\nfor i, row in enumerate(ws.iter_rows(min_row=1, max_row=5, values_only=True)):\n    print(f\"Row {i+1}:\", row)\n# Now print all data rows\nprint(\"\\n--- ALL DATA ---\")\nfor i, row in enumerate(ws.iter_rows(min_row=2, values_only=True)):\n    if any(v is not None for v in row):\n        print(row)\n```\n\nRun this with: python -c \"...\" or save to a temp file and run it."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1598,"cache_read_input_tokens":14418,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1598,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":0,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1ef52651-1d36-4d56-9b85-fb261dce9cac","uuid":"39f68eaf-d5f8-4e98-bff1-28c605be41cb"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_started","task_id":"ad8f1b5a12f979ac0","tool_use_id":"toolu_018SdHHLVGNrA8LrkXVKpGnf","description":"Read Excel vendor data","task_type":"local_agent","prompt":"Read the Excel file at C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx and extract ALL rows from the \"Vendor Analysis Assessment\" sheet. I need:\n1. The exact column headers\n2. Every row of data, specifically the vendor name column and the \"Last 12 months Cost (USD)\" column\n\nUse the Bash tool to run a Python script to read the Excel file and print all rows. Here's the script to run:\n\n```python\nimport openpyxl\nwb = openpyxl.load_workbook(r'C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx', data_only=True)\nprint(\"Sheet names:\", wb.sheetnames)\nws = None\nfor name in wb.sheetnames:\n    if 'Vendor' in name and 'Assessment' in name:\n        ws = wb[name]\n        break\nif ws is None:\n    ws = wb.active\nprint(f\"Using sheet: {ws.title}\")\nprint(f\"Dimensions: {ws.dimensions}\")\n# Print headers (row 1)\nheaders = [cell.value for cell in ws[1]]\nprint(\"Headers:\", headers)\n# Print first 5 rows to understand structure\nfor i, row in enumerate(ws.iter_rows(min_row=1, max_row=5, values_only=True)):\n    print(f\"Row {i+1}:\", row)\n# Now print all data rows\nprint(\"\\n--- ALL DATA ---\")\nfor i, row in enumerate(ws.iter_rows(min_row=2, values_only=True)):\n    if any(v is not None for v in row):\n        print(row)\n```\n\nRun this with: python -c \"...\" or save to a temp file and run it.","uuid":"d08f7402-30ed-4a81-8b01-9bf7bd2d5605","session_id":"1ef52651-1d36-4d56-9b85-fb261dce9cac"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Read the Excel file at C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx and extract ALL rows from the \"Vendor Analysis Assessment\" sheet. I need:\n1. The exact column headers\n2. Every row of data, specifically the vendor name column and the \"Last 12 months Cost (USD)\" column\n\nUse the Bash tool to run a Python script to read the Excel file and print all rows. Here's the script to run:\n\n```python\nimport openpyxl\nwb = openpyxl.load_workbook(r'C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx', data_only=True)\nprint(\"Sheet names:\", wb.sheetnames)\nws = None\nfor name in wb.sheetnames:\n    if 'Vendor' in name and 'Assessment' in name:\n        ws = wb[name]\n        break\nif ws is None:\n    ws = wb.active\nprint(f\"Using sheet: {ws.title}\")\nprint(f\"Dimensions: {ws.dimensions}\")\n# Print headers (row 1)\nheaders = [cell.value for cell in ws[1]]\nprint(\"Headers:\", headers)\n# Print first 5 rows to understand structure\nfor i, row in enumerate(ws.iter_rows(min_row=1, max_row=5, values_only=True)):\n    print(f\"Row {i+1}:\", row)\n# Now print all data rows\nprint(\"\\n--- ALL DATA ---\")\nfor i, row in enumerate(ws.iter_rows(min_row=2, values_only=True)):\n    if any(v is not None for v in row):\n        print(row)\n```\n\nRun this with: python -c \"...\" or save to a temp file and run it."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_018SdHHLVGNrA8LrkXVKpGnf","session_id":"1ef52651-1d36-4d56-9b85-fb261dce9cac","uuid":"e3f0e54d-4297-46ab-86c2-832697ab165b","timestamp":"2026-03-20T20:18:23.582Z"}
