okens: 36043\ntool_uses: 2\nduration_ms: 184209</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1ef52651-1d36-4d56-9b85-fb261dce9cac","uuid":"991a4f16-d700-4463-8778-14941a9f282a","timestamp":"2026-03-20T20:21:27.790Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the Excel file at C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx and extract ALL rows from the \"Vendor Analysis Assessment\" sheet. I need:\n1. The exact column headers\n2. Every row of data, specifically the vendor name column and the \"Last 12 months Cost (USD)\" column\n\nUse the Bash tool to run a Python script to read the Excel file and print all rows. Here's the script to run:\n\n```python\nimport openpyxl\nwb = openpyxl.load_workbook(r'C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx', data_only=True)\nprint(\"Sheet names:\", wb.sheetnames)\nws = None\nfor name in wb.sheetnames:\n    if 'Vendor' in name and 'Assessment' in name:\n        ws = wb[name]\n        break\nif ws is None:\n    ws = wb.active\nprint(f\"Using sheet: {ws.title}\")\nprint(f\"Dimensions: {ws.dimensions}\")\n# Print headers (row 1)\nheaders = [cell.value for cell in ws[1]]\nprint(\"Headers:\", headers)\n# Print first 5 rows to understand structure\nfor i, row in enumerate(ws.iter_rows(min_row=1, max_row=5, values_only=True)):\n    print(f\"Row {i+1}:\", row)\n# Now print all data rows\nprint(\"\\n--- ALL DATA ---\")\nfor i, row in enumerate(ws.iter_rows(min_row=2, values_only=True)):\n    if any(v is not None for v in row):\n        print(row)\n```\n\nRun this with: python -c \"...\" or save to a temp file and run it.","agentId":"ad8f1b5a12f979ac0","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the complete extraction from the \"Vendor Analysis Assessment\" sheet.\n\n---\n\n**Sheet:** `Vendor Analysis Assessment`\n**Dimensions:** A1:E814 (813 rows of data after the header)\n\n**Column Headers (5 co